00:38:06,350 --> 00:38:07,884
You... you'd just end up
killing everyone

718
00:38:07,918 --> 00:38:09,386
yourselves included.

719
00:38:09,419 --> 00:38:12,856
We...<i> they</i> didn't
think so.

720
00:38:12,889 --> 00:38:15,559
They consider the
USA a deep target.

721
00:38:15,592 --> 00:38:17,961
The virus has a
very short cycle.

722
00:38:17,994 --> 00:38:19,396
They thought...

723
00:38:19,429 --> 00:38:21,432
it will burn
itself out here

724
00:38:21,465 --> 00:38:23,500
and with the
borders closed

725
00:38:23,533 --> 00:38:26,904
it will never make it
back to the motherland.

726
00:38:26,937 --> 00:38:29,707
JOHN:
It was made

727
00:38:29,740 --> 00:38:32,875
as a tactical weapon
to create a viral firestorm

728
00:38:32,909 --> 00:38:35,512
that would burn itself
out in North America.

729
00:38:35,545 --> 00:38:37,114
Burn itself out?

730
00:38:37,147 --> 00:38:40,384
The virus. It would die
when it ran out of hosts.

731
00:38:41,485 --> 00:38:43,387
Oh. Well, why would it
run out of hosts?

732
00:38:43,420 --> 00:38:45,122
Because...

733
00:38:45,155 --> 00:38:49,126
it kills them all.

734
00:38:49,159 --> 00:38:50,794
Because this guy Serge Kurbsky
invented it

735
00:38:50,827 --> 00:38:52,963
doesn't mean he has anything
to do with it now.

736
00:38:52,996 --> 00:38:55,666
Bin Laden probably stole
or bought the virus

737
00:38:55,699 --> 00:38:57,568
from the old Soviet stockpiles.

738
00:38:57,601 --> 00:38:59,103
Well, I don't know.

739
00:38:59,136 --> 00:39:01,638
Now, Yuri said that Serge
married an Iraqi woman

740
00:39:01,671 --> 00:39:05,008
in the early 80s, and then when
the Soviet Union broke apart

741
00:39:05,041 --> 00:39:07,845
they moved to Iraq,
where later his wife was killed

742
00:39:07,878 --> 00:39:09,947
in a U.S. bombing raid
over Baghdad.

743
00:39:09,980 --> 00:39:11,715
Now, how's that for motive?

744
00:39:11,748 --> 00:39:14,051
Larry.

745
00:39:11,748 --> 00:39:14,051
Huh?

746
00:39:14,084 --> 00:39:16,486
This is Serge.

747
00:39:16,520 --> 00:39:17,855
Oh, oh. Thank you.

748
00:39:17,888 --> 00:39:19,990
Larry? Larry?

749
00:39:20,023 --> 00:39:21,392
I'm sorry. What?

750
00:39:21,425 --> 00:39:23,527
I still don't see the connection

751
00:39:23,560 --> 00:39:26,397
between Kurbsky and Bin Laden
in Afghanistan.

752
00:39:26,430 --> 00:39:27,798
Well, maybe there isn't one.

753
00:39:27,831 --> 00:39:30,167
Maybe the whole
fatwa/Afghanistan connection

754
00:39:30,200 --> 00:39:31,902
was a deliberate misdirect.

755
00:39:31,935 --> 00:39:35,572
Maybe we bombed the wrong
country. I don't know.

756
00:39:35,605 --> 00:39:37,741
Hold on.

757
00:39:37,774 --> 00:39:39,877
Do you have
yesterday's paper?

758
00:39:39,910 --> 00:39:42,145
Of course.

