888
00:46:57,480 --> 00:46:58,548
I'll be ready. Sir?

889
00:46:58,581 --> 00:47:00,050
Yeah?

890
00:47:00,083 --> 00:47:01,985
There are a lot of rumors
flying around.

891
00:47:09,359 --> 00:47:12,863
The JCS and the CIA think that
Kurbsky may be working for

892
00:47:12,896 --> 00:47:15,498
or with the knowledge of
the Russian military.

893
00:47:15,531 --> 00:47:18,201
That can't be right.

894
00:47:18,234 --> 00:47:20,002
Why?

895
00:47:20,036 --> 00:47:22,072
Since the election,
it's been a political nightmare.

896
00:47:22,105 --> 00:47:24,908
The Communists and the
Nationalists control the Duma.

897
00:47:24,941 --> 00:47:26,442
No one controls the military.

898
00:47:26,476 --> 00:47:28,211
Look at the
sequence of events:

899
00:47:28,244 --> 00:47:30,180
the proliferation
of a bio-weapon

900
00:47:30,213 --> 00:47:32,082
by a Russian
military scientist;

901
00:47:32,115 --> 00:47:34,350
the early closing of
the Russian borders;

902
00:47:34,384 --> 00:47:36,386
the stonewalling
of any information

903
00:47:36,419 --> 00:47:38,020
connected with the virus;

904
00:47:38,054 --> 00:47:41,191
and finally, the Russian
military on high alert

905
00:47:41,224 --> 00:47:43,994
possibly providing
protection for
Iraqi troops

906
00:47:45,094 --> 00:47:46,396
moving toward Kuwait
and Saudi Arabia.

907
00:47:46,429 --> 00:47:48,131
For what... for what purpose?

908
00:47:48,164 --> 00:47:50,066
First step for a
new Russian empire.

909
00:47:50,099 --> 00:47:51,968
That's insane.

910
00:47:52,001 --> 00:47:53,203
Absolutely.

911
00:47:53,236 --> 00:47:57,007
But the question
is-- is it true?

912
00:48:01,444 --> 00:48:04,348
(<i> men talking indistinctly</i> )

913
00:48:11,020 --> 00:48:12,322
MAN:
Yeah? Who is it?

914
00:48:12,355 --> 00:48:13,490
FBI.

915
00:48:16,359 --> 00:48:18,295
Have you seen this man?

916
00:48:18,328 --> 00:48:20,397
No. Never seen him.

917
00:48:20,430 --> 00:48:21,531
No?

918
00:48:21,564 --> 00:48:22,598
What'd he do?

919
00:48:22,632 --> 00:48:23,667
Nothing. Yet.

920
00:48:23,700 --> 00:48:25,935
Sorry to bother you.

921
00:48:28,705 --> 00:48:30,674
<i> Larry...</i>

922
00:48:30,707 --> 00:48:32,609
LARRY (<i> over phone</i> ):<i>
 Ah, fine.</i>

923
00:48:32,642 --> 00:48:34,611
<i>Listen, I've been going crazy.
 Are you all right?</i>

924
00:48:34,644 --> 00:48:36,379
It's chaos;
hundreds are coming in.

925
00:48:36,412 --> 00:48:38,580
We're totally overwhelmed.
It's-it's horrible.

926
00:48:38,614 --> 00:48:41,051
Judy, listen to me.
I want you out of Chicago.

927
00:48:41,084 --> 00:48:42,618
Now, I've arranged
transportation...

928
00:48:42,652 --> 00:48:44,120
Don't be silly.
I can't leave.

929
00:48:44,153 --> 00:48:45,321
Well, you can't stay.

930
00:48:45,355 --> 00:48:46,523
The fatality rate is near 100%.

931
00:48:46,556 --> 00:48:48,491
Once you get it.

932
00:48:48,524 --> 00:48:50,125
Everyone who's been exposed
to the powder has gotten it

933
00:48:50,159 --> 00:48:51,728
so you got to get out of there
right now.

934
00:48:51,761 --> 00:48:53,196
Well, the powder's long gone.

935
00:48:53,229 --> 00:48:54,397
It's spreading its disease now.

936
00:48:54,430 --> 00:48:56,132
There are precautions.

937
00:48:56,165 --> 00:48:57,433
Judy, I've arranged
to get you out of there, okay?

938
00:48:57,467 --> 00:48:59,002
Larry, listen to me.
I'm staying.

939
00:48:59,035 --> 00:49:02,439
It's my job.

940
00:49:06,509 --> 00:49:10,981
Jude, listen,
I understand what you're saying.

941
00:49:11,014 --> 00:49:13,350
I understand it's your job.

942
00:49:13,383 --> 00:49:15,018
But I cannot bear

943
00:49:15,051 --> 00:49:17,520
the idea of something
happening to you.

944
00:49:17,553 --> 00:49:19,089
I'm fine. Don't worry.

945
00:49:19,122 --> 00:49:21,024
You taking all the precautions?

946
00:49:21,057 --> 00:49:23,292
You doing everything
you need to do?

947
00:49:23,326 --> 00:49:25,395
Yes. We know what we're doing.

948
00:49:30,033 --> 00:49:31,969
How is Peter and Timmy?

949
00:49:33,603 --> 00:49:35,439
Not good.

950
00:49:36,639 --> 00:49:38,541
And Abigale?

951
00:49:38,574 --> 00:49:44,414
I think the nanny took her over
to Peter's sister's house.

952
00:49:45,615 --> 00:49:47,149
Have you, uh... have you
unpacked everything

953
00:49:47,183 --> 00:49:48,518
at the house?

954
00:49:48,551 --> 00:49:51,254
No. I can't seem
to find the time.

955
00:49:51,287 --> 00:49:52,422
Judy, come on.

956
00:49:52,455 --> 00:49:54,624
Let's go.

957
00:49:52,455 --> 00:49:54,624
I got to go.

958
00:49:54,657 --> 00:49:56,693
All right.

959
00:49:56,726 --> 00:49:58,361
I love you.

960
00:49:58,394 --> 00:50:00,564
I love you, too.

961
00:50:12,775 --> 00:50:14,444
You all right?

962
00:50:14,477 --> 00:50:17,113
Yeah. I'm
just worried.

963
00:50:17,146 --> 00:50:20,684
Judy's in Chicago
at ground zero.

964
00:50:22,185 --> 00:50:23,787
Well, if I have any extra time,
I'll check up on her.

965
00:50:23,820 --> 00:50:25,188
You going to Chicago?

966
00:50:25,221 --> 00:50:26,790
The Chicago police
have a suspect.

967
00:50:26,823 --> 00:50:28,424
I'm heading out
to question him.

968
00:50:28,458 --> 00:50:29,592
Good luck.

969
00:50:29,625 --> 00:50:31,261
Yeah.

970
00:50:38,568 --> 00:50:40,403
Hey, thanks.

