I mean, you really looked--

977
00:50:54,750 --> 00:50:57,754
don't you think you'd see
the eyes of a madman?

978
00:50:57,787 --> 00:50:59,489
(<i> chuckles</i> )

979
00:50:59,522 --> 00:51:01,124
I doubt it.

980
00:51:01,157 --> 00:51:06,162
You don't think
much of humanity, do you?

981
00:51:06,195 --> 00:51:08,098
Not really, no.

982
00:51:08,131 --> 00:51:10,333
Neither does your virus.

983
00:51:10,366 --> 00:51:12,134
Oh, it's hardly mine.

984
00:51:12,168 --> 00:51:14,838
Marburg has a good mind
of its own.

985
00:51:14,871 --> 00:51:17,273
Where's it from?

986
00:51:17,306 --> 00:51:19,442
The Kiddam Cave
in Northern Kenya.

987
00:51:19,475 --> 00:51:21,411
Why do they
call it Marburg?

988
00:51:21,444 --> 00:51:22,745
Marburg's in Germany.

989
00:51:22,778 --> 00:51:24,781
Why don't they
call it Kiddam?

990
00:51:24,814 --> 00:51:28,350
It's always named after the town
that had the first outbreak.

991
00:51:28,384 --> 00:51:29,853
Marburg?

992
00:51:29,886 --> 00:51:32,422
An infected lab monkey
was shipped from Kenya

993
00:51:32,455 --> 00:51:36,326
to a research complex
at Marburg.

994
00:51:36,359 --> 00:51:40,297
People got sick.

995
00:51:40,897 --> 00:51:42,732
What year
was that?

996
00:51:42,765 --> 00:51:44,600
1968.

997
00:51:51,707 --> 00:51:53,442
That was the year
my father died.

998
00:51:53,476 --> 00:51:55,245
That's correct.

999
00:51:55,278 --> 00:51:58,381
So he wasn't working for
the judge advocate general?

1000
00:51:58,414 --> 00:52:02,619
No. Army intelligence.

1001
00:52:02,652 --> 00:52:03,920
Yeah, see, I...

1002
00:52:03,953 --> 00:52:07,190
you know,
I'd heard that around

1003
00:52:07,223 --> 00:52:10,127
and it sounded true.

1004
00:52:13,429 --> 00:52:15,698
Your father
was sent to Marburg

1005
00:52:15,731 --> 00:52:19,202
to collect a sample
of the virus for our lab.

1006
00:52:21,270 --> 00:52:23,506
Did he succeed?

1007
00:52:23,539 --> 00:52:24,674
Oh, uh...

1008
00:52:24,707 --> 00:52:26,576
in a way.

1009
00:52:27,910 --> 00:52:30,379
He got sick.

1010
00:52:30,413 --> 00:52:32,515
That's what killed him.

1011
00:52:32,548 --> 00:52:35,185
The heart attack story
was just a cover.

1012
00:52:48,397 --> 00:52:50,200
That why my mother hates you?

1013
00:52:50,233 --> 00:52:52,769
In part.

1014
00:52:52,802 --> 00:52:54,804
What's the other part?

1015
00:52:57,273 --> 00:53:00,310
I took a piece of his liver
back to Virginia

1016
00:53:00,343 --> 00:53:01,743
to cultivate the virus.

1017
00:53:01,777 --> 00:53:04,847
Your, uh...

1018
00:53:04,880 --> 00:53:09,186
mother considered that
in poor taste.

1019
00:53:34,310 --> 00:53:36,879
I haven't always done
what's right.

1020
00:53:36,912 --> 00:53:38,680
I know that.

1021
00:53:38,714 --> 00:53:42,884
But, uh...

1022
00:53:42,918 --> 00:53:45,855
I loved my brother very much.

1023
00:53:45,888 --> 00:53:50,660
Your mother
never forgave me.

1024
00:53:50,693 --> 00:53:53,530
And I should?

1025
00:54:02,972 --> 00:54:05,008
MAN:<i>
 We just got lucky is all.</i>

1026
00:54:05,041 --> 00:54:08,745
He tried to leave the stadium
through an illegal exit.

1027
00:54:08,778 --> 00:54:10,279
Mmm.

1028
00:54:10,313 --> 00:54:11,748
Guard told him he
couldn't go that way

1029
00:54:11,781 --> 00:54:13,049
he started
swinging at him.

1030
00:54:13,082 --> 00:54:15,718
So they tussled,
and he was arrested.

1031
00:54:15,751 --> 00:54:17,587
He would have
been released

1032
00:54:17,620 --> 00:54:20,690
but he wouldn't speak,
so we couldn't I.D. him.

1033
00:54:21,357 --> 00:54:22,025
Didn't say boo.

1034
00:54:22,058 --> 00:54:23,993
Some of the boys
down here

1035
00:54:24,026 --> 00:54:25,995
