01:00:06,301 --> 01:00:09,805
our political, military,
and economic infrastructure

1136
01:00:09,838 --> 01:00:11,273
will survive and recover.

1137
01:00:11,306 --> 01:00:14,010
And if we do sustain
another bio-hit?

1138
01:00:15,310 --> 01:00:16,980
I don't know.

1139
01:00:21,884 --> 01:00:24,987
Do you know where
Dr. Rosenberg is?

1140
01:00:25,020 --> 01:00:26,956
No, I'm sorry.

1141
01:00:29,224 --> 01:00:31,094
I'll be right back.

1142
01:00:32,461 --> 01:00:33,828
Hey.

1143
01:00:33,862 --> 01:00:36,366
Larry said you
might come by.

1144
01:00:36,965 --> 01:00:38,801
How are you?

1145
01:00:38,834 --> 01:00:40,970
Well, you know.

1146
01:00:41,003 --> 01:00:42,138
What's it like out there?

1147
01:00:42,171 --> 01:00:44,839
Oh... it is like Ecuador
after a bloody coup.

1148
01:00:44,873 --> 01:00:46,776
I mean,
the streets are empty.

1149
01:00:46,809 --> 01:00:48,444
Army everywhere.

1150
01:00:48,477 --> 01:00:51,212
People rioting, trying to get
the hell out of the city.

1151
01:00:51,246 --> 01:00:52,815
Most people are holed up.

1152
01:00:52,848 --> 01:00:54,316
Many dead?

1153
01:00:54,349 --> 01:00:56,719
Well, there's a full-time
fire at the landfill.

1154
01:00:56,752 --> 01:00:58,387
And you?
How are you doing?

1155
01:00:58,420 --> 01:01:03,059
Uh, I heard that you
have a test to check
for the virus.

1156
01:01:04,426 --> 01:01:06,162
Yes, we've been using it to
screen medical personnel.

1157
01:01:06,195 --> 01:01:07,329
Can you test me?

1158
01:01:07,362 --> 01:01:10,733
Is there any
particular reason?

1159
01:01:16,371 --> 01:01:18,240
I have a confession
to make.

1160
01:01:18,273 --> 01:01:19,475
Mm-hmm.

1161
01:01:19,508 --> 01:01:22,178
I never got you guys
a wedding present.

1162
01:01:22,211 --> 01:01:23,245
You have a year.

1163
01:01:23,278 --> 01:01:24,245
From the wedding?

1164
01:01:24,279 --> 01:01:25,381
Mm-hmm.

1165
01:01:25,414 --> 01:01:27,083
Oh, great.
The shops are closed.

1166
01:01:27,116 --> 01:01:28,984
I thought I'd have to go out
and loot something.

1167
01:01:29,017 --> 01:01:30,152
You'd loot for us?

1168
01:01:30,185 --> 01:01:32,822
That's so sweet.

1169
01:01:35,924 --> 01:01:38,227
Omega 27?

1170
01:01:38,260 --> 01:01:39,762
Larry Sullivan, please.

1171
01:01:41,196 --> 01:01:42,464
M.J. here.

1172
01:01:42,498 --> 01:01:45,868
Yeah, I'm at
the hospital.

1173
01:01:45,901 --> 01:01:48,738
She's sitting right
in front of me.

1174
01:01:48,771 --> 01:01:50,740
Looks good.

1175
01:01:50,773 --> 01:01:53,142
She always looks good.

1176
01:01:53,175 --> 01:01:57,080
Yeah, you should know that
Abdus Hamdoon died in prison

1177
01:01:58,247 --> 01:02:00,182
before we got any
information out of him.

1178
01:02:00,215 --> 01:02:02,284
Uh, I'm going to be
here for...?

1179
01:02:02,317 --> 01:02:03,953
Two hours.

1180
01:02:03,986 --> 01:02:05,254
At least
another two hours.

1181
01:02:05,287 --> 01:02:07,323
Yeah, okay.

1182
01:02:07,356 --> 01:02:08,758
Hold on.

1183
01:02:08,791 --> 01:02:10,826
You want me to go
for a walk?

1184
01:02:10,859 --> 01:02:12,795
No, no. You wait here.
I can get it outside.

1185
01:02:14,029 --> 01:02:15,097
Hey, honey.

1186
01:02:15,130 --> 01:02:16,899
LARRY:
Hey.

1187
01:02:16,932 --> 01:02:18,433
You all right?

1188
01:02:18,467 --> 01:02:21,270
I wish you would stop
asking me that. I feel fine.

1189
01:02:22,571 --> 01:02:24,038
I'm sorry. It's just hanging out
with my uncle all week

1190
01:02:24,072 --> 01:02:26,175
I've come to realize how
important family is.

1191
01:02:26,208 --> 01:02:28,144
Especially the ones
who aren't blood-related.

1192
01:02:28,177 --> 01:02:30,312
Everybody feels that way
about their family.

1193
01:02:30,345 --> 01:02:32,448
No. Not everyone has my family.

1194
01:02:34,349 --> 01:02:35,785
Lar?

1195
01:02:35,818 --> 01:02:38,187
Yeah?

1196
01:02:38,220 --> 01:02:41,890
Do you know how much I love you?

1197
01:02:42,524 --> 01:02:43,926
How happy you've made me?

1198
01:02:43,959 --> 01:02:46,562
How much it means for me
to be your wife?

1199
01:02:46,595 --> 01:02:50,031
Honey...

1200
01:02:50,065 --> 01:02:52,869
i... is something the matter?

1201
01:02:54,536 --> 01:02:58,040
Besides the whole damn world?

1202
01:02:58,073 --> 01:02:59,141
Judy...

1203
01:02:59,174 --> 01:03:00,409
Larry?

1204
01:03:00,442 --> 01:03:02,845
(<i> static</i> )

1205
01:03:00,442 --> 01:03:02,845
Judy? Judy?

1206
01:03:02,878 --> 01:03:05,014
Larry?

1207
01:03:06,915 --> 01:03:09,051
Judy! Judy!

1208
01:03:10,285 --> 01:03:13,356
It's the entire Chicago system.

1209
01:03:18,994 --> 01:03:20,162
He said &quot;Think about it.

1210
01:03:20,195 --> 01:03:21,564
How does it know?&quot;

1211
01:03:21,597 --> 01:03:23,432
Okay. It's going to be dark
in three hours.

1212
01:03:23,465 --> 01:03:25,501
The rain is letting up.
I need your help.

1213
01:03:25,534 --> 01:03:26,869
Shoot.

1214
01:03:26,902 --> 01:03:28,070
If you were Serge Kurbsky

1215
01:03:28,103 --> 01:03:30,406
what would be your target
in the city?

1216
01:03:30,439 --> 01:03:34,176
Well, he has a fat ego.

1217
01:03:34,209 --> 01:03:35,578
I say the president.

1218
01:03:35,611 --> 01:03:37,479
Okay. The White House.
Let's assume that.

1219
01:03:37,512 --> 01:03:39,582
Now, where would he have to be
to release the powder?

1220
01:03:39,615 --> 01:03:41,482
Well, he'd have to be high
above the city.

1221
01:03:41,516 --> 01:03:43,586
Then you'd have to know
how the powder drifts.

1222
01:03:43,619 --> 01:03:44,987
Rate, spread, dispersion.

1223
01:03:45,020 --> 01:03:46,088
You know that, don't you?

1224
01:03:46,121 --> 01:03:47,990
Please, I wrote the book.

1225
01:03:48,023 --> 01:03:49,592
You'd also have to know
the weather conditions.

1226
01:03:49,625 --> 01:03:52,027
Well, this was planned months
in advance

1227
01:03:52,060 --> 01:03:54,997
so how would you predict
the weather that far ahead?

1228
01:03:55,030 --> 01:03:57,900
You'd have to look back
a few years to conditions

1229
01:03:57,933 --> 01:03:59,602
in the month you wanted
to release.

1230
01:03:59,635 --> 01:04:02,471
Winds, inversions, temperature--
take an average.

1231
01:04:02,504 --> 01:04:04,406
Courtesy National
Weather Service.

1232
01:04:04,439 --> 01:04:05,575
Let's go find him.

1233
01:04:46,949 --> 01:04:48,951
MAN (<i> over TV</i> ):
22 are now confirmed dead

1234
01:04:48,984 --> 01:04:51,220
at the Arlington
Memorial Bridge.

1235
01:04:51,253 --> 01:04:53,222
Over 200 people,
ignoring the curfew

1236
01:04:53,255 --> 01:04:54,590
had gathered at the bridge

1237
01:04:54,623 --> 01:04:56,425
in an attempt to cross
into Virginia.

1238
01:04:56,458 --> 01:04:58,994
After failing to disperse
the crowd with tear gas

1239
01:04:59,027 --> 01:05:01,397
the National Guard fired
live rounds into the crowd.

1240
01:05:01,430 --> 01:05:03,132
Has to be more east.

1241
01:05:03,165 --> 01:05:04,967
What, you don't
believe me, no?

1242
01:05:05,000 --> 01:05:06,435
No. You're using
the best case.

1243
01:05:06,468 --> 01:05:07,937
We tested it
20 years ago.

1244
01:05:07,970 --> 01:05:09,504
It was just
not that impressive.

1245
01:05:09,538 --> 01:05:10,606
Oh, well, yes.

1246
01:05:10,639 --> 01:05:12,141
Back in the Black Ages.

1247
01:05:12,174 --> 01:05:13,175
But some of us

1248
01:05:13,208 --> 01:05:15,678
continued to work, no?

1249
01:05:16,445 --> 01:05:17,346
Continued to perfect.

1250
01:05:17,380 --> 01:05:19,048
I've seen your perfection;
I still say east.

1251
01:05:19,081 --> 01:05:20,282
(<i> speaking Russian</i> )

1252
01:05:20,315 --> 01:05:21,216
Oh, up yours!

1253
01:05:21,249 --> 01:05:22,484
Shut up! Shut up!!

1254
01:05:22,517 --> 01:05:24,185
Just shut up.

1255
01:05:24,219 --> 01:05:26,221
Now, can you both agree
that we're close?

1256
01:05:26,254 --> 01:05:27,356
Close, yes.

1257
01:05:27,389 --> 01:05:29,024
Definitely close.

1258
01:05:29,057 --> 01:05:30,459
(<i> speaking Russian</i> )

1259
01:05:30,492 --> 01:05:34,163
(<i> dialing phone</i> )

1260
01:05:36,164 --> 01:05:38,167
Yeah, Sullivan here.

1261
01:05:38,200 --> 01:05:41,002
We're going to set up a general
surveillance on 16th and M.

1262
01:05:42,504 --> 01:05:44,339
All right. I'm going to
go have a look around

1263
01:05:44,373 --> 01:05:46,008
get familiar
with the area.

1264
01:05:46,041 --> 01:05:47,242
Look around?

1265
01:05:47,275 --> 01:05:48,677
What are we
supposed to do?

1266
01:05:48,710 --> 01:05:50,646
Just sit here and
wait to breathe

1267
01:05:50,679 --> 01:05:52,081
something nasty?

1268
01:05:58,687 --> 01:06:00,589
This crazy.

1269
01:06:00,622 --> 01:06:02,024
(<i> sighs</i> )

1270
01:06:02,057 --> 01:06:04,392
I'll, uh...
I'll talk to him.

1271
01:06:09,731 --> 01:06:11,333
JOHN:
Hold on!

1272
01:06:11,366 --> 01:06:12,501
Larry!

1273
01:06:12,534 --> 01:06:13,602
Wait a minute.

1274
01:06:13,635 --> 01:06:15,270
You know he's right.

1275
01:06:15,303 --> 01:06:17,506
There's nothing
for Yuri and me
to do here.

1276
01:06:17,539 --> 01:06:19,308
There's nothing
for<i> you</i> to do.

1277
01:06:19,341 --> 01:06:21,143
Yeah, we're
going to wait.

1278
01:06:21,176 --> 01:06:22,344
We're going to wait
and we're going to see.

1279
01:06:22,377 --> 01:06:23,645
For what?

1280
01:06:23,678 --> 01:06:25,681
I don't know, but
being in a shelter

1281
01:06:25,714 --> 01:06:28,049
with our heads up our asses
isn't going to do us any good.

1282
01:06:28,083 --> 01:06:29,685
Neither will
vomiting up blood.

1283
01:06:29,718 --> 01:06:32,388
I don't care.

1284
01:06:32,421 --> 01:06:35,124
Oh, I see.

1285
01:06:35,157 --> 01:06:36,125
That's it.

1286
01:06:36,158 --> 01:06:37,593
You want to punish us.

1287
01:06:37,626 --> 01:06:39,294
You want to punish me.

1288
01:06:39,327 --> 01:06:42,398
It's an ugly
world, Larry

1289
01:06:42,431 --> 01:06:44,299
and we're an ugly race

1290
01:06:44,332 --> 01:06:47,469
but if making me the big bad man
helps, you go right ahead.

1291
01:06:47,502 --> 01:06:49,505
Join the crowd;
blame Uncle John.

1292
01:06:49,538 --> 01:06:51,373
I had a life.

1293
01:06:51,406 --> 01:06:53,241
Now, I don't know how
much is left of it

1294
01:06:53,275 --> 01:06:55,177
and you're right,
I probably blame
you for that.

1295
01:06:55,210 --> 01:06:56,545
I blame you for
my partner's death

1296
01:06:56,578 --> 01:06:58,413
and the death
of his little boy.

1297
01:06:58,447 --> 01:07:00,115
I blame you for my father,
a man I never knew.

1298
01:07:00,148 --> 01:07:01,750
But if anything were
to happen to Judy--

1299
01:07:01,783 --> 01:07:04,053
the person I love more
than anybody in the world--

1300
01:07:04,086 --> 01:07:06,055
I'd blame you so much,
I'd probably kill you.

1301
01:07:06,088 --> 01:07:08,090
Now, I want you to go
back, sit in the car

1302
01:07:08,123 --> 01:07:09,491
with your buddy and wait.

1303
01:07:09,524 --> 01:07:11,560
And God willing,
there's something to do

1304
01:07:11,593 --> 01:07:13,295
we'll do it.

1305
01:07:19,201 --> 01:07:20,736
(<i> car door opening</i> )

1306
01:07:20,769 --> 01:07:22,471
(<i> car door closes</i> )

1307
01:07:22,504 --> 01:07:23,839
Just shut up.

1308
01:07:23,872 --> 01:07:26,808
Just sit there
and keep your damn mouth shut.

1309
01:07:29,444 --> 01:07:32,681
WOMAN (<i> over P.A.</i> ):
Dr. Temple, report to O.R.

1310
01:07:32,714 --> 01:07:34,417
Dr. Temple to O.R.

1311
01:07:46,728 --> 01:07:48,497
I'm ready.

1312
01:07:50,532 --> 01:07:52,468
You're infected.

1313
01:07:55,270 --> 01:07:57,673
(<i> sighs</i> )

1314
01:08:01,510 --> 01:08:05,681
Oh, what a stupid way to die,
huh?

1315
01:08:06,848 --> 01:08:09,551
There's always a chance
the test is wrong.

1316
01:08:09,584 --> 01:08:11,553
There's a chance you
could beat the odds...

1317
01:08:11,586 --> 01:08:13,354
Judy, come on.

1318
01:08:13,388 --> 01:08:15,757
I know what the odds are.

1319
01:08:15,790 --> 01:08:19,828
I've seen up close
what this virus does to people.

1320
01:08:21,729 --> 01:08:23,866
(<i> sobbing</i> )

1321
01:08:28,203 --> 01:08:29,638
(<i> sniffling</i> )

1322
01:08:33,441 --> 01:08:35,410
(<i> sobbing</i> )

1323
01:08:35,443 --> 01:08:38,347
(<i> voice cracking</i> ):
It's all right to cry.

1324
01:08:38,880 --> 01:08:40,683
(<i> crying</i> )

1325
01:08:43,551 --> 01:08:45,487
Crying's okay.

1326
01:08:45,520 --> 01:08:47,623
(<i> sniffling</i> )

1327
01:09:04,406 --> 01:09:07,309
(<i> whispering</i> ):
Come on, let's go, come on.

1328
01:09:08,210 --> 01:09:09,478
All right,
I'll see you later.

1329
01:09:09,511 --> 01:09:10,613
Okay, bye.

1330
01:09:17,886 --> 01:09:20,189
(<i> door opens</i> )

1331
01:09:25,894 --> 01:09:27,829
Where have you been?

1332
01:09:27,862 --> 01:09:28,897
Out.

1333
01:09:28,930 --> 01:09:31,700
Get back here!

1334
01:09:31,733 --> 01:09:33,702
You must be crazy.

1335
01:09:33,734 --> 01:09:36,237
Do you want
to get the sickness?

1336
01:09:36,270 --> 01:09:37,505
What is that?

1337
01:09:37,538 --> 01:09:38,473
What?

1338
01:09:38,506 --> 01:09:39,441
<i> That.</i>

1339
01:09:39,474 --> 01:09:40,475
Nothing.

1340
01:09:40,508 --> 01:09:41,876
Show me.

1341
01:09:49,818 --> 01:09:52,754
You could have been shot.

1342
01:09:52,787 --> 01:09:54,323
Batteries!

1343
01:09:54,356 --> 01:09:55,958
You would get shot
for batteries?!

1344
01:09:55,991 --> 01:09:57,626
Are you stupid?

1345
01:09:57,659 --> 01:10:00,295
What are you going to do
with those batteries?

1346
01:10:00,328 --> 01:10:01,263
Trade them.

1347
01:10:01,296 --> 01:10:02,331
For what?

1348
01:10:01,296 --> 01:10:02,331
Food.

1349
01:10:02,364 --> 01:10:03,432
We don't need food.

1350
01:10:03,465 --> 01:10:04,633
Medicine.

1351
01:10:04,666 --> 01:10:06,401
They'll give us those things!

1352
01:10:06,434 --> 01:10:08,704
No, they won't. In Chevy Chase,
they will, not here.

1353
01:10:08,737 --> 01:10:10,505
They'll let the sickness come

1354
01:10:10,538 --> 01:10:11,839
and let us starve.
They hate us!

1355
01:10:11,873 --> 01:10:13,008
You're crazy.

1356
01:10:13,041 --> 01:10:14,343
That's what
everyone says.

1357
01:10:14,376 --> 01:10:15,944
That doesn't make it true!

1358
01:10:15,977 --> 01:10:18,013
But they say the politicians
and the rich people

1359
01:10:18,046 --> 01:10:19,414
are moving to Virginia.

1360
01:10:19,447 --> 01:10:21,350
That Virginia is clean.

1361
01:10:21,383 --> 01:10:23,719
So you think a little river
is going to keep Virginia clean

1362
01:10:23,752 --> 01:10:26,722
if D.C.'s dirty?

1363
01:10:26,755 --> 01:10:29,358
Go to your room.

1364
01:10:29,391 --> 01:10:30,759
Go. Listen to music.

1365
01:10:30,792 --> 01:10:31,994
Go be a boy.

1366
01:10:32,027 --> 01:10:34,529
You know how they died?

1367
01:10:34,562 --> 01:10:35,797
You know
how Dad died?

1368
01:10:35,830 --> 01:10:37,032
Your guts split open
inside of you

1369
01:10:37,065 --> 01:10:38,700
and you start to
bleed to death.

1370
01:10:38,733 --> 01:10:40,769
You just want to sit here
and wait to die

1371
01:10:40,802 --> 01:10:41,870
just like Dad did.

1372
01:10:41,903 --> 01:10:43,405
Where are
you going?
Out.

1373
01:10:43,438 --> 01:10:44,439
Get back here!

1374
01:10:44,472 --> 01:10:45,540
Don't go...

1375
01:10:45,573 --> 01:10:46,775
Oakley!

1376
01:10:46,808 --> 01:10:49,311
Don't go! Oakley!

1377
01:10:49,644 --> 01:10:50,746
Oakley!

1378
01:10:50,779 --> 01:10:52,514
Oakley!

1379
01:10:52,547 --> 01:10:54,383
Oakley!

1380
01:10:54,416 --> 01:10:56,318
Oakley!

1381
01:11:10,565 --> 01:11:13,635
(<i> people moaning and coughing</i> )

1382
01:11:44,666 --> 01:11:47,869
Hey! You're
not supposed
to be in here.

1383
01:11:47,902 --> 01:11:50,772
FBI.

1384
01:11:50,805 --> 01:11:53,108
It's your funeral.

1385
01:11:53,141 --> 01:11:54,809
Let's go.

1386
01:12:18,099 --> 01:12:19,468
(<i> gunshot</i> )

1387
01:12:26,408 --> 01:12:28,577
DOCTOR:
We're doing everything we can.

1388
01:12:28,610 --> 01:12:32,580
WOMAN (<i> over PA</i> ):
Dr. Williams, report
to Emergency, stat.

1389
01:12:32,614 --> 01:12:34,715
Dr. Williams to Emergency, stat.

1390
01:12:34,749 --> 01:12:36,518
(<i> woman whimpering</i> )

1391
01:12:37,552 --> 01:12:39,821
Hi.

1392
01:12:39,854 --> 01:12:44,025
Do you remember me?

1393
01:12:44,058 --> 01:12:46,428
I'm Peter's
sister, Patty.

1394
01:12:46,461 --> 01:12:47,996
Yes, of course, I do.

1395
01:12:48,029 --> 01:12:52,101
Do you know
about Peter and Timmy?

1396
01:12:52,534 --> 01:12:54,436
Yes.

1397
01:12:54,469 --> 01:12:57,773
How do you feel?

1398
01:12:57,806 --> 01:13:00,808
It's.... it's
about Abigale.

1399
01:13:01,443 --> 01:13:02,644
Is Abigale sick?

1400
01:13:02,677 --> 01:13:06,081
The nanny, Hela,
was supposed

1401
01:13:06,114 --> 01:13:09,116
to bring her
to my house

1402
01:13:09,150 --> 01:13:11,553
but she never did.

1403
01:13:11,586 --> 01:13:15,758
I think Hela thought that
Abigale was infected.

1404
01:13:17,091 --> 01:13:19,528
So Abigale is still with
the nanny at Peter's house.

1405
01:13:19,561 --> 01:13:24,098
No, I don't think the
nanny's there anymore.

1406
01:13:24,132 --> 01:13:28,169
You think Abigale is alone
in the house?

1407
01:13:32,807 --> 01:13:35,510
Promise me you'll find Abigale.

1408
01:13:40,014 --> 01:13:42,418
Promise me.

1409
01:14:06,741 --> 01:14:09,011
(<i> dog barks in distance</i> )

1410
01:14:29,898 --> 01:14:31,600
Hello?

1411
01:14:33,568 --> 01:14:36,672
Abigale?

1412
01:14:37,071 --> 01:14:39,708
Sweetheart?

1413
01:14:39,741 --> 01:14:41,810
It's okay, honey.

1414
01:14:41,843 --> 01:14:43,779
(<i> dog barks in distance</i> )

1415
01:14:45,113 --> 01:14:46,648
Sweetie?

1416
01:14:49,083 --> 01:14:53,722
Abigale? Love?

1417
01:14:53,755 --> 01:14:55,090
It's all right.

1418
01:15:03,331 --> 01:15:04,933
Abigale.

1419
01:15:08,836 --> 01:15:11,139
(<i> helicopter flies overhead</i> )

1420
01:15:12,040 --> 01:15:13,141
(<i> dialing beeps</i> )

1421
01:15:15,176 --> 01:15:16,912
WOMAN:
CNN. How may I direct your call?

1422
01:15:16,945 --> 01:15:18,980
Hello? CNN?

1423
01:15:19,013 --> 01:15:20,549
Yes?

1424
01:15:20,582 --> 01:15:22,951
Good. It is Serge Kurbsky.

1425
01:15:22,984 --> 01:15:28,891
I want to talk to the reporter
Robert Poll, please.

1426
01:15:31,693 --> 01:15:34,095
CNN is reporting
that Kurbsky has

1427
01:15:34,128 --> 01:15:37,098
the Marburg Influenza
biological weapon

1428
01:15:37,131 --> 01:15:39,768
and is giving the residents
of DC four hours to evacuate.

1429
01:15:40,234 --> 01:15:41,235
Old trick, huh?

1430
01:15:41,269 --> 01:15:43,772
He wants as many people
on the street as possible

1431
01:15:43,805 --> 01:15:45,274
to increase infection.

1432
01:15:50,044 --> 01:15:51,880
WOMAN:
Hurry, let's go!

1433
01:15:56,651 --> 01:15:58,820
(<i> people shouting</i> )

1434
01:16:03,257 --> 01:16:05,661
MAN:
Come on! Come on! Come on!

1435
01:16:10,365 --> 01:16:12,200
David, David!
Come on! Come on!

1436
01:16:31,219 --> 01:16:35,090
MAN:
Get out of here!
Let's block off down there!

1437
01:16:37,925 --> 01:16:39,995
34th and M! We got the trace!
Let's go!

1438
01:16:41,162 --> 01:16:43,732
Let's go, let's go, let's go!

1439
01:16:48,836 --> 01:16:52,107
(<i> car horns blaring</i> )

1440
01:16:53,808 --> 01:16:57,846
MAN (<i> over bullhorn</i> ):
Return to your homes!

1441
01:16:58,713 --> 01:17:00,215
There is a curfew in effect!

1442
01:17:00,248 --> 01:17:03,751
You will be arrested!
Return to your homes!

1443
01:17:03,785 --> 01:17:06,821
Return to your homes!
There is a curfew in effect!

1444
01:17:06,854 --> 01:17:08,123
You will be arrested!

1445
01:17:13,461 --> 01:17:15,330
(<i> people yelling</i> )

1446
01:17:15,363 --> 01:17:17,633
Come on! This way!

1447
01:17:19,033 --> 01:17:21,102
Stay away from the barricades!

1448
01:17:21,135 --> 01:17:22,904
We will open fire!

1449
01:17:22,937 --> 01:17:24,039
Stand back!

1450
01:17:24,072 --> 01:17:27,075
Stay away from the barricades!

1451
01:17:27,108 --> 01:17:29,444
We will open fire! Stay back!

1452
01:17:29,477 --> 01:17:31,012
Let's get
out of here!

1453
01:17:31,045 --> 01:17:32,380
(<i> crowd chanting</i> ):
We want shelter!

1454
01:17:32,413 --> 01:17:35,750
We want shelter!
We want shelter!

1455
01:17:35,783 --> 01:17:38,854
Come on! Get out!

1456
01:17:48,496 --> 01:17:52,200
Wake up. Wake up, Noel.
Don't die on me, please.

1457
01:18:05,079 --> 01:18:08,817
6876 M Street.
Yeah, it's a block away.

1458
01:18:10,151 --> 01:18:12,821
They got a trace a block away.
Hang tight.

1459
01:18:12,854 --> 01:18:14,723
(<i> helicopter flies overhead</i> )

1460
01:18:29,437 --> 01:18:31,172
FBI. Have you seen this man?

1461
01:18:31,205 --> 01:18:32,841
No!

1462
01:18:38,780 --> 01:18:41,049
FBI. Have you seen this man?

1463
01:18:41,082 --> 01:18:42,050
Have you?

1464
01:18:42,083 --> 01:18:43,084
I think so. I...

1465
01:18:43,117 --> 01:18:44,419
Where?

1466
01:18:44,452 --> 01:18:47,455
I think he rented
Tom's place. Top floor.

1467
01:18:47,488 --> 01:18:48,990
Number 43.

1468
01:19:48,916 --> 01:19:51,019
(<i> heavy sigh</i> )

1469
01:20:00,561 --> 01:20:02,531
(<i> helicopter flies overhead</i> )

1470
01:20:23,417 --> 01:20:26,054
FBI! Freeze!

1471
01:20:27,421 --> 01:20:29,491
Put down the container!

1472
01:20:30,524 --> 01:20:33,028
Put down
the container!

1473
01:20:58,019 --> 01:20:58,653
Get back!

1474
01:20:58,686 --> 01:21:00,188
It's a bomb!

1475
01:21:01,222 --> 01:21:03,224
It's a bomb! Get away!

1476
01:21:03,257 --> 01:21:05,160
(<i> crowd screams</i> )

1477
01:21:27,381 --> 01:21:29,184
Did it crack open?

1478
01:21:31,719 --> 01:21:34,122
Is not broken.

1479
01:21:43,364 --> 01:21:45,467
We live, no?

1480
01:21:47,234 --> 01:21:48,670
For now.

1481
01:21:50,404 --> 01:21:52,474
(<i> grunting</i> )

1482
01:22:46,761 --> 01:22:49,364
Mom, I missed you, Mom.

1483
01:23:04,445 --> 01:23:05,480
Hey!

1484
01:23:05,513 --> 01:23:06,581
Hey, hey!

1485
01:23:09,550 --> 01:23:10,752
Thank you.

1486
01:23:13,387 --> 01:23:15,723
Thank you, thank you.

1487
01:23:15,756 --> 01:23:17,525
Congratulations.

1488
01:23:19,360 --> 01:23:20,661
FARRELL:
Sullivan.

1489
01:23:20,694 --> 01:23:23,398
Good job, good job.

1490
01:23:23,431 --> 01:23:25,165
God bless America!

1491
01:23:25,199 --> 01:23:28,135
(<i> all cheer</i> )

1492
01:23:28,169 --> 01:23:30,138
Zenkovsky just arrived.

1493
01:23:32,139 --> 01:23:35,443
Wait. What are you saying?

1494
01:23:35,476 --> 01:23:37,077
Where the hell
are the backup generators?

1495
01:23:37,111 --> 01:23:39,547
Doesn't anything work
in this damn place?

1496
01:23:39,580 --> 01:23:42,817
Maybe we should hold a seance;
find out what happens next.

1497
01:23:42,850 --> 01:23:44,585
AGENT:
They've done it.

1498
01:23:44,618 --> 01:23:46,754
Iraq just crossed the border
into Saudi Arabia.

1499
01:23:46,787 --> 01:23:48,790
The Saudis are rolling over.

1500
01:23:50,324 --> 01:23:51,392
Have we responded?

1501
01:23:51,425 --> 01:23:52,493
I-I don't know.

1502
01:23:52,526 --> 01:23:54,128
What about the Russians?

1503
01:23:54,161 --> 01:23:56,364
I don't know.

1504
01:23:56,397 --> 01:23:59,233
I'm still trying
to call Chicago.

1505
01:23:59,266 --> 01:24:02,603
So when are the
lines going to
be operational?

1506
01:24:02,636 --> 01:24:05,139
Well, who the
hell would know?

1507
01:24:05,172 --> 01:24:06,840
It might take a while.

1508
01:24:06,874 --> 01:24:09,110
There's nobody left
to maintain the lines
or man the boards.

1509
01:24:09,143 --> 01:24:10,545
Do you have any
communications?

1510
01:24:10,578 --> 01:24:12,080
Short wave.

1511
01:24:12,113 --> 01:24:13,347
Okay. I want to get
hooked up with my wife.

1512
01:24:13,380 --> 01:24:14,749
She's at Metropolitan Hospital.

1513
01:24:14,782 --> 01:24:16,217
I want to get hooked up
with her right now.

1514
01:24:16,250 --> 01:24:17,618
Metropolitan Hospital
is shut down.

1515
01:24:17,651 --> 01:24:19,287
She won't be there.

1516
01:24:19,320 --> 01:24:20,788
Uh, a message to M.J.

1517
01:24:20,821 --> 01:24:23,358
If I can get
a message to M.J....

1518
01:24:23,824 --> 01:24:27,128
No. She's dead.

1519
01:24:31,832 --> 01:24:34,469
I'm sorry.

1520
01:24:36,270 --> 01:24:38,639
Is there a flight? Anything?
A military flight?

1521
01:24:38,672 --> 01:24:41,375
The whole place is shut down
to air traffic, Larry.

1522
01:24:52,786 --> 01:24:54,755
Back to the hotel?

1523
01:24:54,788 --> 01:24:56,691
No. Home. Chicago.

1524
01:24:59,426 --> 01:25:02,130
Did you hear, uh,
Iraq invaded Saudi Arabia?

1525
01:25:02,163 --> 01:25:05,266
Mm'mm.

1526
01:25:05,299 --> 01:25:07,201
So what will you do?

1527
01:25:07,234 --> 01:25:09,737
Oh, I thought
I'd stick around DC

1528
01:25:09,770 --> 01:25:11,439
help out if I can.

1529
01:25:11,472 --> 01:25:12,907
I know you can.

1530
01:25:12,940 --> 01:25:15,343
(<i> elevator bell dings,
 door opens</i> )

1531
01:25:19,413 --> 01:25:20,882
Hope she's okay.

1532
01:25:20,915 --> 01:25:22,684
Thank you.

1533
01:25:45,806 --> 01:25:47,909
(<i> turns radio on</i> )

1534
01:25:47,942 --> 01:25:50,745
(<i> garbled static</i> )

1535
01:26:43,497 --> 01:26:45,767
Judy!

1536
01:26:57,811 --> 01:27:01,749
Judy...

1537
01:27:02,516 --> 01:27:04,352
Judy... Judy, darling.

1538
01:27:08,389 --> 01:27:11,259
You're all right? Hmm?

1539
01:27:11,292 --> 01:27:12,994
Yeah.

1540
01:27:14,061 --> 01:27:15,996
Abigale had the flu,
but we're fine.

